From: ws@xivic.bo.open.de (Wolfgang Schelongowski)
Subject: Re: interesting proposition
Date: Fri, 20 Aug 93 09:18:22 MEST

ashley@cco.caltech.edu (Allen M. Ashley) writes:

> Someone who wants to implement the user map idea should set up
> an email address to process the responses. Every response should start
> with the zip code of the responder,

So e.g. the zip code 60327 designates an area in Frankfurt am Main,
Germany ? ;-)

The zip code alone is not sufficient. You need a country prefix like
>us< for anybody from the USA, >de< for Germany, ... >st< for Sao Tome
and Principe.

And do _not_ assume anything about the zip code. I've heard that the
British have a blank space as significant part of the zip code
(like 4YX 5TG != 4YX5 TG). Be prepared to deal with such kind of
atrocities committed by the national post boards.

>                                     and all responses should be indexed
> on the zip code.

Yes, indeed.

